# Scale-out knob for peak-bandwidth experiments:
# Increase the number of SM clusters while keeping the traced ISA (SM86).
#
# This is useful when the memory backend (e.g., long tREAD HBF) requires more
# memory-level parallelism (MLP) than a small GPU can generate.
-gpgpu_n_clusters 92
-gpgpu_n_cores_per_cluster 1
